snippet.textDisplay:
'When I am weak,
You give me strength,
You give me hope,
When I am down,
In the face of darkness,
You are my guide,
You are my love,
My love divine.
Help me forgive,
When I am hurt,
Help me believe,
When I am lost,
In times of trouble,
You ease my weary mind,
You are my love,
My love divine.'

If this seems beautiful to you, then I am sorry you have not read poetry in English! Listen to Dylan, Morrison, Joan Baez, and countless others. It's not about what you want to say, it's how you say it!
